1
00:00:18,052 --> 00:00:21,052
I WOULD LIKE
A DOUBLE-DIP VANILLA
WITH GRANOLA SPRINKLES, PLEASE.

2
00:00:22,423 --> 00:00:26,258
- TRUCK AIN'T OPEN.
- UH, I HAVE CASH MONEY.

3
00:00:28,329 --> 00:00:30,329
IT'S 7:30
IN THE FREAKIN' MORNING.

4
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:32,397
WHY DON'T YOU TRY
THE WAFFLE HOUSE?

5
00:00:32,466 --> 00:00:36,234
CONSIDERING THE IRON,
CALCIUM AND LACTOSE
IN THE ICE CREAM,

6
00:00:36,303 --> 00:00:40,171
<i>THE CARBOHYDRATE VALUE OF</i>
<i>THE CONE AND THE FIBER CONTENT</i>
<i>OF THE GRANOLA,</i>

7
00:00:40,241 --> 00:00:44,509
ONE COULD, IN REALITY, RECEIVE
MORE NUTRITIOUS INGREDIENTS
IN ONE TASTY SURPRISE...

8
00:00:44,578 --> 00:00:46,945
THAN IN AN ENTIRE
BACON AND EGG BREAKFAST.

9
00:00:47,013 --> 00:00:51,383
- ARE YOU SOME KIND OF NUT?
- NO. I JUST LIKE ICE CREAM.

10
00:00:51,452 --> 00:00:53,752
YEAH.

11
00:01:31,524 --> 00:01:35,060
- TAXI!
-<i> [ Man ] I DON'T UNDERSTAND.</i>

12
00:01:35,128 --> 00:01:37,963
THE POLICE LOOKED THROUGH MY
DAUGHTER'S ROOM ONCE ALREADY.

13
00:01:38,031 --> 00:01:41,833
<i>WHAT DID YOU SAY</i>
<i>YOUR NAME WAS?</i>
WAXMAN. DETECTIVE JAROD WAXMAN.

14
00:01:41,902 --> 00:01:45,103
<i>THE OTHER OFFICER SAID</i>
<i>A TEENAGER MISSING</i>
<i>LESS THAN 48 HOURS...</i>

15
00:01:45,172 --> 00:01:47,773
<i>WASN'T GONNA BE</i>
<i>A HIGH PRIORITY CASE.</i>

16
00:01:47,842 --> 00:01:50,242
WE RECONSIDERED
THE SITUATION.

17
00:01:50,311 --> 00:01:52,577
<i>WAS THERE ANYTHING</i>
<i>OUT OF ORDINARY GOING ON...</i>

18
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:55,246
IN YOUR DAUGHTER'S LIFE
BEFORE SHE DISAPPEARED?

19
00:01:55,315 --> 00:01:57,516
SOMETHING BOTHERING HER?

20
00:01:57,584 --> 00:02:00,419
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>MY WIFE PASSED AWAY</i>
<i>THREE YEARS AGO.</i>

21
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:03,588
- CANCER.
- I'M SORRY.

22
00:02:03,657 --> 00:02:06,991
<i>AND IT'S BEEN HARD FOR ME,</i>
<i>BUT NOT LIKE IT'S BEEN</i>
<i>FOR JESSE.</i>

23
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,993
<i>SHE JUST BARELY TURNED 15.</i>

24
00:02:09,063 --> 00:02:11,629
<i>SHE WAS AT AN AGE WHERE A GIRL</i>
<i>REALLY NEEDS HER MOTHER.</i>

25
00:02:11,698 --> 00:02:15,434
<i>AND I GUESS I JUST DIDN'T HAVE</i>
<i>THE ANSWERS THAT SHE NEEDED.</i>

26
00:02:15,503 --> 00:02:17,703
MAYBE SHE WENT AWAY
WITH A FRIEND,
SOMEONE FROM SCHOOL?

27
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:20,105
<i>JESSE'S SHY.</i>
<i>SHE DOESN'T HAVE</i>
<i>MUCH OF A SOCIAL LIFE.</i>

28
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:23,709
<i>I DON'T KNOW.</i>
<i>IT'S LIKE SHE JUST</i>
<i>VANISHED INTO THIN AIR.</i>

29
00:02:23,777 --> 00:02:25,844
SHE SEEMED TO HAVE
A SPECIAL INTEREST IN ANGELS.

30
00:02:25,913 --> 00:02:28,279
YEAH. WHEN HER MOTHER
PASSED AWAY,

31
00:02:28,348 --> 00:02:31,516
<i>JESSE STARTED COLLECTING THEM,</i>
<i>READING BOOKS ABOUT THEM.</i>

32
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:33,885
THAT ONE'S HER FAVORITE.

33
00:02:39,893 --> 00:02:43,495
- HAVE YOU SEEN THIS BEFORE?
- NO, NEVER.

34
00:02:43,564 --> 00:02:45,530
"GATES OF HELL."

35
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:48,333
<i>THAT'S JESSE'S HANDWRITING.</i>
<i>YOU'VE GOT TO HELP ME.</i>

36
00:02:48,402 --> 00:02:50,568
MY DAUGHTER'S LIFE
IS IN YOUR HANDS, DETECTIVE.

37
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:58,610
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

38
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,079
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

39
00:03:01,147 --> 00:03:04,415
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

40
00:03:04,484 --> 00:03:07,886
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

41
00:03:07,955 --> 00:03:11,389
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

42
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,658
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

43
00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:16,494
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

44
00:03:16,563 --> 00:03:18,563
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

45
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:21,533
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

46
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,581
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

47
00:03:52,999 --> 00:03:55,933
<i>A MAN WITH NO FACE?</i>

48
00:03:56,002 --> 00:03:58,736
IT REMINDS ME OF A YOUNG MAN
I RECENTLY HIRED...

49
00:03:58,805 --> 00:04:02,307
<i>TO HELP RESTORE</i>
<i>A BROKEN-DOWN OLD WAX MUSEUM.</i>

50
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:06,411
MR. KLEINMAN,
I DIDN'T EVEN HEAR YOU COME IN.
[ Chuckling ]

51
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,680
OH, A GIFT FOR A FRIEND?

52
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:11,015
MORE LIKE... A MESSAGE.

53
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,151
AH. I BROUGHT YOU A SNACK.

54
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:16,788
OOH, I HOPE IT'S ICE CREAM.
BETTER. A DELICACY.

55
00:04:16,857 --> 00:04:18,923
<i>ALCATRAZ OYSTERS.</i>

56
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:22,360
<i>THESE LITTLE BEAUTIES YOU CAN</i>
<i>FIND ONLY IN SAN FRANCISCO BAY.</i>

57
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:24,529
GO AHEAD. EAT.

58
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:27,598
<i>ENJOY. YEAH.</i>

59
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:37,008
- EH?
- MMM.

60
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,177
<i> THEY'RE VERY GOOD.</i>
[ Chuckling ]

61
00:04:40,347 --> 00:04:42,347
[ Sniffs ]

62
00:04:44,384 --> 00:04:49,387
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS JUST MIGHT DO THE TRICK.

63
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:52,190
<i>YOU ARE A VERY STRANGE</i>
<i>YOUNG MAN, JAROD.</i>

64
00:04:52,259 --> 00:04:55,293
NOT HALF AS STRANGE
AS THE PEOPLE
I'M SENDING THIS TO.

65
00:04:55,361 --> 00:04:58,964
JAROD, ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T
WANT TO STAY UPSTAIRS?

66
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:01,466
ACTUALLY, I SPEND
A LOT OF TIME ALONE.

67
00:05:01,535 --> 00:05:03,501
<i> IT'S SORT OF NICE</i>
<i> TO HAVE THE COMPANY.</i>

68
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:08,040
-AH.
-MR. KLEINMAN, HAVE YOU EVER
SEEN ANYTHING LIKE THIS BEFORE?

69
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,877
[ Gasps ]
MY GOD!

70
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:18,683
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

71
00:05:18,752 --> 00:05:21,986
A MAN I KNOW IS SEARCHING
FOR HIS DAUGHTER.

72
00:05:22,055 --> 00:05:25,690
- YOU HAVE SEEN IT.
- YEAH.

73
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:30,595
- I HAVE SEEN IT.
- YOU'RE A HOLOCAUST SURVIVOR.

74
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:34,832
MEMBERS OF THE S.S.
WORE SIMILAR SYMBOLS...

75
00:05:34,901 --> 00:05:36,834
ON THEIR UNIFORMS.

76
00:05:36,904 --> 00:05:39,437
<i>DEVILS. DEMONS.</i>
THIS MAN--

77
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:41,873
<i> HE'S WORRIED</i>
<i> FOR HIS DAUGHTER'S SAFETY.</i>

78
00:05:41,942 --> 00:05:44,008
OH, HE SHOULD BE.

79
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:47,946
HE SHOULD BE SCARED
TO DEATH.

80
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:30,755
<i>♪♪ [ Techno, Man Singing,</i>
<i>     Indistinct ]</i>

81
00:06:30,824 --> 00:06:33,458
♪♪ [ Man Screaming ]

82
00:06:33,527 --> 00:06:36,260
<i>♪♪ [ Singing Resumes ]</i>

83
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:09,860
DIDN'T YOUR MOTHER EVER TELL YOU
IT'S RUDE TO STARE?

84
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,530
I HARDLY KNEW MY MOTHER.

85
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:17,502
SEE SOMETHING YOU LIKE?
I'M CONFUSED.

86
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:21,172
DOESN'T ALL THAT... HURT?
THAT'S THE IDEA, SLICK.

87
00:07:21,241 --> 00:07:24,442
SO YOU ENJOY...
SELF-INFLICTED PAIN?

88
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:27,378
YOU'RE SCREWIN'
WITH MY HEAD, RIGHT?

89
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,782
ACTUALLY,
I'M LOOKING FOR SOMEONE.
A YOUNG MAN. A MAGICIAN.

90
00:07:30,851 --> 00:07:33,351
THROW A ROCK, BABY CAKES.

91
00:07:36,022 --> 00:07:38,723
<i> YEAH, I'VE SEEN HAWK</i>
<i> HANDING THESE OUT</i>
<i> TO A SELECT FEW.</i>

92
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:40,725
HE'S HOLDING COURT
IN THE BACK ROOM.

93
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:42,727
YOU CAN'T MISS HIM.
THANK YOU.

94
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:46,731
AND WHEN YOU'RE FINISHED
PLAYING GAMES WITH
THE BIRD MAN, COME BACK.

95
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:51,168
I'LL SHOW YOU A REAL MAGIC SHOW.
THAT WOULD BE ENJOYABLE.
THANK YOU.

96
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,306
♪♪<i> [ Screaming ]</i>

97
00:07:57,276 --> 00:08:00,978
<i>♪♪ [ Singing Resumes ]</i>

98
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:06,584
MOST PEOPLE CAN'T COMPREHEND
THE VERY WORLD THEY INHABIT.

99
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,653
<i> THEY EXIST,</i>
<i> BUT THEY DON'T EXPERIENCE.</i>

100
00:08:08,722 --> 00:08:10,922
THEY LOOK, BUT THEY NEVER SEE.

101
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:13,091
<i>I BELIEVE THAT THEY'RE PORTALS--</i>

102
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:16,928
WINDOWS TO THE BODY,
THE MIND AND THE SPIRIT.

103
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:21,866
<i>GIVEN THE PERFECT EXCHANGE</i>
<i>OF ENERGIES,</i>
<i>THESE WINDOWS CAN BE OPENED.</i>

104
00:08:21,935 --> 00:08:26,037
<i>PASS BEYOND.</i>
<i>I LOOK AT YOU.</i>

105
00:08:26,106 --> 00:08:28,706
<i> I LOOK INTO YOU,</i>

106
00:08:34,314 --> 00:08:37,715
<i>AND I SEE TREMENDOUS SORROW,</i>
<i>EMPTINESS.</i>

107
00:08:41,321 --> 00:08:44,288
I WANT YOU TO THINK ABOUT
WHAT WAS TAKEN FROM YOU.

108
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:48,626
IMAGINE IN YOUR MIND'S EYE
THE CAUSE OF YOUR SUFFERING.

109
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:54,532
I-- I DON'T--
SHH. TRUST ME.

110
00:08:59,472 --> 00:09:05,277
<i>I WANT YOU TO THINK</i>
<i>ABOUT THE OBJECT OF YOUR PAIN.</i>
<i>CAN YOU SEE IT?</i>

111
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:09,981
YES.

112
00:09:12,653 --> 00:09:17,589
I OFFER YOU THIS GIFT...
WITH ALL MY LOVE.

113
00:09:23,096 --> 00:09:25,096
[ Gasps ]
OH, MY GOD!

114
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,067
<i>HOW COULD YOU--</i>
<i>WHO IS CLARE?</i>

115
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:34,572
SH-SHE'S MY-- MY TWIN SISTER.

116
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:37,275
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

117
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:41,279
AND WHERE IS SHE?
SHE WAS KILLED...

118
00:09:41,347 --> 00:09:45,683
IN A CAR ACCIDENT
WHEN WE WERE TWO.
[ Sobbing ]

119
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:47,752
BUT HOW COULD YOU KNOW THAT?

120
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:51,256
SIMPLE.
YOUR HEART TOLD ME.

121
00:09:58,331 --> 00:10:00,832
TELL US AGAIN ABOUT
THE ANGEL'S FLIGHT.

122
00:10:03,336 --> 00:10:05,303
<i> WHAT'S ANGEL'S FLIGHT?</i>

123
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:10,041
<i>IT WAS A DREAM THE GREAT HOUDINI</i>
<i>HAD REPEATEDLY</i>
<i>THROUGHOUT HIS LIFE.</i>

124
00:10:11,078 --> 00:10:13,011
OR NIGHTMARES, SOME BELIEVE.

125
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:16,714
HOUDINI FELT,
GIVEN THE POWER OF ANGELS,
HE COULD BREAK FREE...

126
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:20,685
<i>FROM THE BOUNDARIES OF EARTH</i>
<i>AND SOAR IN THE HEAVENS</i>
<i>LIKE A GOD.</i>

127
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:24,923
<i>BUT, UNFORTUNATELY, HE WASN'T.</i>

128
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:27,691
AND WHEN HE DIED,
HIS DREAM DIED WITH HIM.

129
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:30,528
<i>HAWK SAYS THE ANGEL'S FLIGHT</i>
<i>IS ATTAINABLE.</i>

130
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:37,335
CLOSE ENOUGH TO TOUCH.

131
00:10:37,404 --> 00:10:41,672
I SUGGEST WE ASSEMBLE AGAIN
AT MIDNIGHT
FOR A READING SESSION.

132
00:10:41,741 --> 00:10:44,041
GO WITH THE ANGELS.

133
00:10:48,715 --> 00:10:53,651
<i>[ Girl ]</i>
<i>THIS IS TOO HEAVY FOR ME.</i>
<i>[ Boy ] THIS GUY IS AWESOME.</i>

134
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:58,356
THEY SEEM TO BE VERY... LOYAL.
I OFFER THEM
SOMETHING THEY NEED.

135
00:11:00,126 --> 00:11:02,060
SOMETHING THEIR WORLDS
HAVE DENIED THEM.
<i>♪♪ [ Techno, Woman Singing ]</i>

136
00:11:02,128 --> 00:11:05,029
MAGIC.
LOVE.

137
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:11,503
MY NAME IS JAROD.
I HEAR YOU HAVE A GREAT GIFT--

138
00:11:11,571 --> 00:11:14,538
THE ABILITY TO TOUCH PEOPLE.

139
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:20,044
AND YOU DESIRE THIS GIFT.
I WISH TO LEARN
FROM THE BEST.

140
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:25,082
AND WHY SHOULD I OPEN MYSELF
TO A STRANGER?

141
00:11:25,151 --> 00:11:30,921
<i>♪ I CAN'T SLEEP</i>
<i>  NO MATTER HOW I TRY ♪</i>

142
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:38,162
<i>♪♪ [ Continues, Indistinct ]</i>

143
00:11:47,006 --> 00:11:50,474
<i>[ Blowing ]</i>
<i>THE PERFECT EXCHANGE OF ENERGY.</i>

144
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:00,718
KESSLER WILL SHOW YOU THE WAY.

145
00:12:01,955 --> 00:12:05,422
<i>♪ AWAKE AT NIGHT ♪</i>

146
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:08,326
<i>♪ AWAKE AT NIGHT ♪</i>

147
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:14,732
MIDNIGHT.
YOU DON'T SEEM TO SHARE HAWK'S
BELIEF IN THE POWER OF ANGELS.

148
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:18,436
- EXCUSE ME?
- WHEN THE SUBJECT
OF ANGEL'S FLIGHT CAME UP,

149
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:21,439
<i>YOU SEEMED RATHER UNCOMFORTABLE.</i>

150
00:12:21,508 --> 00:12:24,442
<i>♪ AWAKE AT NIGHT ♪</i>
MIDNIGHT.

151
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:32,517
<i>♪ I CAN'T SLEEP</i>
<i>  NO MATTER HOW I TRY ♪♪</i>

152
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:34,919
WHERE ARE YOU, FALLEN ANGEL?

153
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:38,289
WHERE ARE YOU?

154
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:49,834
DON'T EVEN TALK TO ME
UNLESS IT'S GOOD NEWS. BROOTS?

155
00:12:52,072 --> 00:12:57,541
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE HAPPY.
IT'S NOT GOOD NEWS.

156
00:12:57,610 --> 00:13:01,813
- ANY SIGN OF JAROD?
- IT'S LIKE HE VANISHED
INTO A BLACK HOLE.

157
00:13:01,881 --> 00:13:05,216
KIND OF LIKE
YOUR PERSONAL LIFE?
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

158
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:08,219
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>THAT'S ODD, ISN'T IT?</i>
<i>[ Miss Parker ] WHAT, THE GIRL?</i>

159
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:10,421
<i>CIGAR.</i>
<i>LYLE DOESN'T SMOKE.</i>

160
00:13:10,489 --> 00:13:13,424
OH, YEAH,
THAT'S A GIFT.

161
00:13:13,493 --> 00:13:17,094
<i> JERRY, THE GUY WITH</i>
<i> THE GLASS EYE WHO WORKS</i>
<i> DOWN IN TRANSPORTATION--</i>

162
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:20,198
WELL, HE TOLD ME
THAT MR. LYLE IS EXPECTING...

163
00:13:20,266 --> 00:13:22,433
<i> SOME CENTRE HOTSHOT</i>
<i> FROM THE WEST COAST.</i>

164
00:13:22,502 --> 00:13:26,437
<i>-[ Miss Parker ] DID MARBLE-EYED</i>
<i> JERRY GIVE YOU A NAME?</i>
-NOT THAT I CAN REMEMBER.

165
00:13:26,506 --> 00:13:30,741
HMM. THAT MAKES HIM ABOUT
AS WORTHLESS AS THIS SHIRT THEN,
DOESN'T IT?

166
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:34,612
WHAT, DID DON HO
HAVE A GARAGE SALE?
DON WHO?

167
00:13:34,681 --> 00:13:36,881
THE BOX. WHAT'S IN IT?

168
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:39,783
OH, YEAH. MISS PARKER,
THIS BOX IS FOR YOU.

169
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:43,855
WELL, THAT'S SOMETHING
YOU DON'T SEE EVERY DAY.

170
00:13:43,923 --> 00:13:47,425
- "BEWARE OF STRANGERS
BEARING GIFTS."
- I BET IT'S FROM JAROD.

171
00:13:47,494 --> 00:13:50,928
GEE, YOU THINK?
MAYBE HE'S TALKIN'
ABOUT LYLE.

172
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:54,765
<i> UH-UH.</i>
<i> CIGARS AND CHAMPAGNE?</i>

173
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:57,168
MAYBE.

174
00:13:57,237 --> 00:13:59,570
WHAT ARE YOU
UP TO NOW, JAROD?

175
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:42,513
<i> [ Door Knob Rattling ]</i>

176
00:14:46,586 --> 00:14:50,154
<i> [ Hawk ]</i>
<i> WELCOME, MY FRIENDS,</i>
<i> TO THE MIDNIGHT SESSION.</i>

177
00:14:52,359 --> 00:14:54,658
LET US BEGIN.

178
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,912
PLEASE STAND.

179
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:32,530
<i>COMMON, I KNOW.</i>
<i>READ THE DATE ON THIS COIN.</i>

180
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:40,004
- 1994.
- 1994.

181
00:15:40,073 --> 00:15:43,207
<i>THAT HAS SPECIAL MEANING</i>
<i>FOR YOU, DOESN'T IT?</i>

182
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:46,544
YES.
WHY?

183
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:50,381
BECAUSE THAT'S THE YEAR
MY MOTHER DIED.

184
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,853
TURN THE COIN OVER.

185
00:15:59,592 --> 00:16:01,525
OH!

186
00:16:04,764 --> 00:16:06,964
SHE-SHE USED TO CALL ME
HER PUPPY.

187
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:11,201
YES. SHE'S WITH YOU.

188
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:13,771
[ Sobbing ]

189
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:18,075
[ Whispering ]
SHE'LL ALWAYS BE WITH YOU.

190
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:22,213
THANK YOU.

191
00:16:22,282 --> 00:16:24,448
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

192
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,623
<i>I SEE YOU FOUND YOUR WAY.</i>

193
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:37,995
-<i> I WASN'T SURE</i>
<i> WHICH WAY TO GO.</i>
-<i> OBVIOUSLY NOT THAT WAY.</i>

194
00:16:38,064 --> 00:16:42,300
TIGHT SECURITY.
PROTECTING MAGIC SECRETS.

195
00:16:42,368 --> 00:16:45,636
<i>HAWK LIKES TO KEEP</i>
<i>HIS PERSONAL LIFE... PERSONAL.</i>

196
00:16:46,873 --> 00:16:48,940
I SUGGEST YOU
JOIN THE OTHERS.

197
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:51,141
THE READING'S ALREADY STARTED.

198
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:54,444
- CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?
- IF I SAID NO,
WOULD YOU WALK AWAY?

199
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:56,514
PROBABLY NOT.

200
00:17:00,387 --> 00:17:02,486
- LOOK FAMILIAR?
- WHERE DID YOU GET THAT?

201
00:17:05,525 --> 00:17:08,959
I LIKE TO KEEP
MY PERSONAL LIFE... PERSONAL.

202
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:10,994
YOU DON'T WANT TO MISS
THE SESSION.

203
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:13,530
OF COURSE NOT.

204
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,672
-<i> [ Hawk ] YOUR NAME?</i>
- UH, SCOTT.

205
00:17:21,741 --> 00:17:26,009
STAND UP, SCOTT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I WON'T BITE.

206
00:17:26,078 --> 00:17:29,179
<i>[ People Chuckling ]</i>

207
00:17:31,684 --> 00:17:33,684
YOU CAN PUT THAT DOWN.

208
00:17:39,959 --> 00:17:42,427
YOU'RE NEW HERE.
YES.

209
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:47,231
YOU'RE NERVOUS.
[ Chuckles ]
A LITTLE BIT.

210
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:51,034
YOU'RE ALSO BLEEDING.
BLEEDING?

211
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,743
INSIDE.

212
00:18:01,347 --> 00:18:03,347
YOU WERE BETRAYED.

213
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:07,484
HURT BY SOMEONE YOU TRUSTED,
SOMEONE YOU LOVED.

214
00:18:08,855 --> 00:18:11,522
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.
YES, YOU DO.

215
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,693
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

216
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:19,029
WE LOVE YOU.
<i> [ People, Softly ]</i>
<i> WE LOVE YOU.</i>

217
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:21,566
[ Gasps ]

218
00:18:21,634 --> 00:18:24,068
YOU COULDN'T BELIEVE IT
WHEN IT STARTED.

219
00:18:24,136 --> 00:18:27,171
<i> YOU WANTED TO SCREAM,</i>
<i> BUT YOU WERE AFRAID.</i>

220
00:18:27,239 --> 00:18:31,175
CONFUSED.
PLEASE DON'T.

221
00:18:31,244 --> 00:18:34,879
<i>[ Hawk ]</i>
<i>YOU WERE SO YOUNG,</i>
<i>VULNERABLE.</i>

222
00:18:34,948 --> 00:18:39,049
<i> IT WAS LIKE A NIGHTMARE</i>
<i> THE WAY HE CAME AT YOU.</i>
<i> SO MUCH ANGER.</i>

223
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,052
I CAN'T DO THIS.

224
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,187
YOU THOUGHT IF
YOU CLOSED YOUR EYES,
IT WOULD STOP.

225
00:18:43,256 --> 00:18:45,256
BUT IT DIDN'T STOP,
DID IT, SCOTT?

226
00:18:45,325 --> 00:18:47,257
IT GOT MORE VIOLENT
AND ANGRY.

227
00:18:47,326 --> 00:18:49,426
NO. NO.

228
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:52,363
<i>[ Hawk ]</i>
<i>YOU WERE AFRAID TO TELL ANYONE.</i>

229
00:18:52,431 --> 00:18:56,700
AFRAID TO SAY THE NAME,
TERRIFIED THAT NO ONE
WOULD BELIEVE YOU.

230
00:18:56,769 --> 00:18:59,737
I WAS AFRAID.
[ Sobbing ]

231
00:18:59,806 --> 00:19:03,975
YOU WERE ONLY A BOY,
AND HE WAS SO POWERFUL,
SO TERRIFYING.

232
00:19:04,043 --> 00:19:06,310
<i>[ Scott ]</i>
<i>I WANTED HIM TO STOP HITTING ME.</i>

233
00:19:06,378 --> 00:19:09,614
<i>I WANTED TO SAY HIS NAME.</i>

234
00:19:09,682 --> 00:19:11,916
I KNOW YOU DID.
AND NOW YOU CAN.

235
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:14,151
NOW YOU CAN SAY IT
FOR THE ENTIRE WORLD TO HEAR.

236
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:17,154
I CAN'T.
SAY IT.

237
00:19:17,223 --> 00:19:19,924
I CAN'T.
SAY IT, SCOTT!

238
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,992
SAY IT AND END
THE NIGHTMARE FOREVER!

239
00:19:22,061 --> 00:19:25,563
I CAN'T!
[ Sobbing Continues ]

240
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:28,665
<i> I CAN'T.</i>

241
00:19:28,734 --> 00:19:32,503
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SAY IT FOR YOU.

242
00:19:32,572 --> 00:19:36,006
<i>[ People Gasping ]</i>
IT WAS YOUR FATHER.

243
00:19:36,075 --> 00:19:38,542
<i>IT WAS YOUR FATHER</i>
<i>WHO BEAT YOU, SCOTT.</i>

244
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:48,186
I NEVER WANTED IT TO HAPPEN.

245
00:19:48,254 --> 00:19:51,755
<i>I KNOW YOU DIDN'T, SCOTT.</i>
<i> I KNOW YOU DIDN'T.</i>

246
00:19:51,824 --> 00:19:54,692
<i>YOU DON'T HAVE TO</i>
<i>BE AFRAID ANYMORE.</i>

247
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,761
<i>IT'S OKAY, SCOTT.</i>

248
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:03,166
YOU SHOULD TRY THAT ON ME.

249
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:07,604
MAYBE I WILL.
YOU THINK YOU HELPED HIM?

250
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:11,709
EVERYONE HAS SECRETS,
DEMONS THEY KEEP HIDDEN.

251
00:20:11,777 --> 00:20:14,611
AND SOMETIMES,
IF YOU DON'T STOP THEM,

252
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,181
THEY EAT YOU ALIVE
A PIECE AT A TIME.

253
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:20,251
WHAT ABOUT YOU, JAROD?

254
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:22,686
WHAT KIND OF DEMONS
ARE YOU HIDING INSIDE?

255
00:20:28,962 --> 00:20:32,196
<i>THAT'S ALL FOR TONIGHT.</i>
<i>MR. KESSLER WILL</i>
<i>COLLECT YOUR OFFERINGS.</i>

256
00:20:39,772 --> 00:20:42,406
ANOTHER RUSH DELIVERY
FROM JAROD?
YEAH, NUMBER THREE.

257
00:20:42,475 --> 00:20:45,810
<i>GREAT. NOW YOUR BOY'S YANKIN'</i>
<i>MY CRANK ON AN HOURLY BASIS.</i>

258
00:20:45,878 --> 00:20:49,813
JAROD NEVER PLAYS THESE GAMES
WITHOUT SUBSTANTIAL MOTIVATION.

259
00:20:49,882 --> 00:20:51,882
IT'S A HEAD MADE OF STERNO.

260
00:20:55,054 --> 00:20:57,955
WHAT IS IT THIS TIME?
WOW!

261
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:01,525
ANOTHER GIANT LEAP
INTO THE TWILIGHT ZONE.

262
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:05,563
YOU WERE SAYING SOMETHING
ABOUT MOTIVATION?

263
00:21:05,631 --> 00:21:07,764
SUBSTANCE, PARKER.

264
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:12,069
AND THERE'S ANOTHER NOTE.
"SEE NO EVIL."

265
00:21:12,138 --> 00:21:15,005
IN THE BOX WITH THE EARS,
THE NOTE WAS, "HEAR NO EVIL."

266
00:21:15,074 --> 00:21:17,808
ANYTHING ELSE ON THE IDENTITY
OF LYLE'S MYSTERY ARRIVAL?

267
00:21:17,877 --> 00:21:19,977
NOTHING ON THE GRAPEVINE.

268
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:26,616
WELL, AT LEAST WE HAVE
MR. POTATO HEAD.

269
00:21:26,685 --> 00:21:29,353
COOL.

270
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,763
[ Beeps ]

271
00:22:29,782 --> 00:22:32,549
<i>I FINALLY FOUND YOU, JESSICA.</i>

272
00:23:38,984 --> 00:23:40,917
KILL THE SON OF A BITCH.

273
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:57,600
<i>I WAS EXCITED</i>
<i>TO GET YOUR CALL,</i>
<i>EVEN IF IT WAS A BIT CRYPTIC.</i>

274
00:23:57,669 --> 00:24:00,537
FOUND SOMETHING OUT
ABOUT JESSICA?
I'M STILL WORKING ON THE CASE.

275
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:05,142
MR. BRACKEN, YOU TOLD ME
THAT YOUR WIFE...

276
00:24:05,211 --> 00:24:07,143
PASSED AWAY FROM AN ILLNESS.

277
00:24:07,212 --> 00:24:12,783
THAT'S RIGHT.
THAT'S NOT WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED, IS IT?

278
00:24:12,852 --> 00:24:17,020
I WANNA HELP YOU
FIND YOUR DAUGHTER,
BUT WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

279
00:24:17,089 --> 00:24:20,157
IF I'M GOING TO HELP YOU,
YOU HAVE TO TELL ME THE TRUTH.

280
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,061
OKAY.

281
00:24:28,367 --> 00:24:31,468
SARAH WAS... VIBRANT.

282
00:24:31,537 --> 00:24:35,905
SHE WAS SO FULL OF LIFE.
THEN SHE GOT SICK.

283
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:39,910
ALL THAT LIFE JUST
SLOWLY DRAINED OUT OF HER.

284
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:43,580
SHE TRIED TO TAKE
THE TREATMENT,
BUT... IT WAS TOO LATE.

285
00:24:43,649 --> 00:24:46,850
I DON'T KNOW WHY
SHE WENT OUT ON THAT ROOF.

286
00:24:46,919 --> 00:24:51,421
I DON'T KNOW... WHAT SHE
WAS THINKING WHEN SHE JUMPED.

287
00:24:52,792 --> 00:24:55,793
THE POLICE FOUND HER BODY
IN THE ALLEY THE NEXT MORNING.

288
00:24:58,364 --> 00:25:01,632
SHE WAS STILL CLUTCHING
HER ANGEL PENDANT IN HER HAND.

289
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,769
AND THAT'S HOW JESSE
BECAME OBSESSED WITH ANGELS.

290
00:25:05,838 --> 00:25:09,873
YEAH. I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE
TOLD YOU THE TRUTH.

291
00:25:09,942 --> 00:25:14,512
I JUST, UH, DIDN'T THINK
THAT IT--

292
00:25:14,580 --> 00:25:20,016
FIND MY LITTLE GIRL,
DETECTIVE, PLEASE.
SHE'S ALL I HAVE LEFT.

293
00:25:25,757 --> 00:25:28,025
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> SPEAK NO EVIL.</i>

294
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:34,631
ANYBODY RECOGNIZE HIM?
HE KINDA LOOKS
LIKE GILLIGAN.

295
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:36,833
GILLIGAN?
YEAH.

296
00:25:36,902 --> 00:25:41,405
YOU KNOW, THE SKIPPER
AND THE PROFESSOR
AND MARY ANN AND-AND GINGER.

297
00:25:41,473 --> 00:25:43,941
YOU GREW UP IN A TRAILER PARK,
DIDN'T YOU?

298
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:47,244
NO, I DID NOT.
IT WAS A MOBILE HOME.

299
00:25:47,313 --> 00:25:50,414
<i>IT'S OBVIOUS JAROD</i>
<i>IS TRYING TO KEEP US BUSY</i>
<i>CHASING MR. NO NAME'S IDENTITY,</i>

300
00:25:50,483 --> 00:25:52,782
WHILE HE SKIPS ALONG
FREE AS HE PLEASES.

301
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:55,819
- THE QUESTION IS,
WHY ALL THE EFFORT?
- WHAT ABOUT THE NOTES?

302
00:25:55,888 --> 00:25:59,890
- JOKES WITHOUT PUNCH LINES.
- MAYBE A WARNING.

303
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:06,897
WHAT IS THAT?
IT LOOKS LIKE
A-A WATER STAIN.

304
00:26:06,966 --> 00:26:08,966
[ Sniffs ]
EW!

305
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:14,271
- SMELLS LIKE LOW TIDE.
- [ Sniffs ] WOW!
THEY ALL SMELL THE SAME.

306
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:17,808
<i>MAYBE JAROD'S JUST</i>
<i>DROPPING BREAD CRUMBS.</i>

307
00:26:17,876 --> 00:26:20,444
HAVE THESE CARDS ANALYZED.
OKAY.

308
00:26:23,748 --> 00:26:26,650
WHO ARE YOU, PAL?

309
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:45,569
<i>"A HISTORY OF FALLEN ANGELS."</i>

310
00:26:48,507 --> 00:26:53,209
FALLEN... ANGELS.

311
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,545
HAWK SAYS THE ANGEL'S FLIGHT
IS ATTAINABLE.

312
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:57,815
CLOSE ENOUGH TO TOUCH.

313
00:26:57,883 --> 00:27:01,418
<i>[ Echoing ]</i>

314
00:27:01,487 --> 00:27:05,088
I DON'T KNOW WHY
SHE WENT OUT ON THAT ROOF.
I DON'T KNOW...

315
00:27:05,157 --> 00:27:08,324
WHAT SHE WAS THINKING
WHEN SHE JUMPED.

316
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:26,203
[ Squeaking ]

317
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:03,006
JESSICA.

318
00:29:04,643 --> 00:29:07,243
[ Gun Cocks ]
I HOPED YOU WERE SMARTER.

319
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:11,515
WHY COULDN'T YOU JUST WALK AWAY
AND LET THIS THING FINISH?

320
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:14,284
THE SAME REASON
THAT YOU COULDN'T SIT
AT THAT TABLE WITH HAWK...

321
00:29:14,353 --> 00:29:16,419
AND TALK ABOUT ANGEL'S FLIGHT.

322
00:29:16,488 --> 00:29:19,356
HE DID THIS, DIDN'T HE?
WHAT HAPPENED?

323
00:29:20,559 --> 00:29:23,560
<i>JESSE BRACKEN</i>
<i>DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TO OFFER?</i>

324
00:29:23,629 --> 00:29:26,529
OR SHE FOUND THE COMPUTER FILES
THAT HAWK KEEPS ON THE OTHERS?

325
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:28,632
<i>THE WEALTHY, DISENFRANCHISED,</i>
<i>YOUNG PEOPLE...</i>

326
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,167
THAT WERE RECRUITED
OFF THE STREETS BY YOU.

327
00:29:31,236 --> 00:29:35,271
<i>THAT'S THE GAME, ISN'T IT?</i>
<i>DAZZLE THEM WITH MAGIC,</i>

328
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:37,441
AND THEN TAKE THEM
FOR EVERY PENNY YOU CAN.

329
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:40,176
I TOLD HAWK THAT WE
SHOULD JUST CUT AND RUN,

330
00:29:40,245 --> 00:29:43,012
<i> BUT IT WAS NEVER ONLY</i>
<i> ABOUT THE MONEY FOR HIM.</i>

331
00:29:43,081 --> 00:29:47,117
ANGEL'S FLIGHT WAS JUST
THE LAST ACT OF THE PLAY.

332
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:53,956
I SWEAR, SOMETIMES,
THE GUY REALLY THINKS
HE'S GONNA FLY.

333
00:29:54,025 --> 00:29:58,962
- WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?
-<i> HAWK FLIPPED OUT</i>
<i> A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO,</i>

334
00:29:59,030 --> 00:30:01,698
AND JESSE OVERHEARD US
TALKIN' ABOUT THE SCAM.

335
00:30:01,767 --> 00:30:04,701
<i> I JUST THOUGHT HE WAS</i>
<i> GONNA TALK TO HER.</i>

336
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:12,542
- WHAT?
- SHE'S STILL ALIVE.

337
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:24,854
-<i> GIVE ME THE GUN AND HELP ME</i>
<i>  GET HER OUT OF HERE.</i>
- NO. HAWK--

338
00:30:24,922 --> 00:30:27,724
IF YOU LET HER DIE,
THERE IS NO MAGIC IN THE WORLD
THAT'S GOING TO SAVE YOU.

339
00:30:27,792 --> 00:30:31,160
- NOW GIVE ME THE GUN.
- ALL SHE WANTED...

340
00:30:31,229 --> 00:30:35,532
WAS SOMEBODY
TO CARE ABOUT HER,
SOMEBODY TO WATCH OVER HER.

341
00:30:38,803 --> 00:30:42,738
SOMEBODY DID.
NOW GIVE ME THE GUN.

342
00:31:17,242 --> 00:31:19,242
<i>♪ IT'S REVOLUTION ♪</i>

343
00:31:20,312 --> 00:31:24,180
<i>♪ IN THE TOWN WATCHING IT GROW ♪</i>

344
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:28,118
<i>♪ IT'S REVOLUTION ♪</i>

345
00:31:28,186 --> 00:31:31,520
<i>♪♪ [ Continues, Indistinct ]</i>

346
00:31:49,107 --> 00:31:52,008
<i>♪ IT'S REVOLUTION ♪</i>

347
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:10,926
<i>♪ IT'S REVOLUTION ♪♪</i>

348
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:24,607
<i>MISS PARKER, NOT ONLY HAS JAROD</i>
<i>TOPPED OFF MR. POTATO HEAD</i>
<i>WITH A NICE HAIRPIECE,</i>

349
00:32:24,676 --> 00:32:28,477
I JUST FOUND OUT
THAT THE STAINS ON THE CARDS
WERE MADE BY OYSTERS.

350
00:32:28,546 --> 00:32:30,780
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>OYSTERS?</i>
MM-HMM.

351
00:32:30,849 --> 00:32:32,849
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
JAROD WAS A SLOPPY EATER?

352
00:32:32,918 --> 00:32:35,651
THE RESIDUE WAS LEFT
BY A VERY SPECIFIC SHELLFISH...

353
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,720
FOUND ONLY
IN THE SAN FRANCISCO BAY.

354
00:32:37,788 --> 00:32:40,889
<i> I THINK JAROD WANTED</i>
<i> US TO FIND HIM.</i>

355
00:32:40,958 --> 00:32:43,059
SAN FRANCISCO IS A BIG CITY.

356
00:32:43,127 --> 00:32:45,194
WELL, I STARTED THINKING
ABOUT THE HEAD JAROD LEFT,

357
00:32:45,263 --> 00:32:47,396
SO I SCRAPED SOME OF THE WAX,
AND I HAD IT ANALYZED.

358
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:52,368
IT IS USED ALMOST EXCLUSIVELY
FOR THE CONSTRUCTION
OF HUMAN REPLICATION.

359
00:32:52,437 --> 00:32:55,138
WAX MUSEUM.
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>TOUCHÉ, SYD.</i>

360
00:32:55,207 --> 00:32:58,140
SO I CALLED THE FRISCO AREA
AND FOUND ONE DEFUNCT
WAX MUSEUM.

361
00:32:58,209 --> 00:33:02,712
AND WHEN I CALLED,
THIS IS WHAT I GOT.

362
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:07,049
[ Jarod ]
HELLO, SYDNEY, BROOTS,
AND AS ALWAYS, MISS PARKER.

363
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:09,485
I ASSUME SINCE YOU'RE LISTENING
TO THIS RECORDING,

364
00:33:09,554 --> 00:33:11,487
YOU FIGURED OUT
MY CURRENT LOCATION.

365
00:33:11,556 --> 00:33:13,690
I REALIZE THINGS GOT
A LITTLE FISHY ALONG THE WAY,

366
00:33:13,758 --> 00:33:15,891
<i>BUT YOU REALIZE TIMING</i>
<i>IS EVERYTHING...</i>

367
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:18,227
IN THE "RUN FOR YOUR LIFE"
BUSINESS.

368
00:33:18,296 --> 00:33:21,164
I WON'T KEEP YOU
LONGER THAN NECESSARY.

369
00:33:21,232 --> 00:33:23,199
I REALIZE YOU HAVE
A PLANE TO CATCH.

370
00:33:23,268 --> 00:33:26,335
<i>I JUST ASK TWO THINGS:</i>
<i>FIRST, BRING ALONG THE WAX HEAD.</i>

371
00:33:26,404 --> 00:33:28,704
<i>I THINK YOU'LL</i>
<i>FIND IT ENLIGHTENING.</i>

372
00:33:28,773 --> 00:33:32,441
AND SECOND, DON'T FORGET
TO BUCKLE YOUR SEAT BELTS.
HAPPY LANDINGS.

373
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:36,112
-<i> GOOD WORK, BROOTS.</i>
- THANKS, SYDNEY.

374
00:33:36,181 --> 00:33:38,548
LET'S NOT POLISH EACH OTHER'S
DOORKNOBS QUITE YET.

375
00:33:38,617 --> 00:33:41,283
- GET THE JET FIRED UP.
WE'RE GOING TO CALIFORNIA.
- YES, MA'AM.

376
00:33:41,352 --> 00:33:44,521
- BROOTS?
- YES, MA'AM?

377
00:33:44,589 --> 00:33:48,558
- DON'T WEAR THAT SHIRT.
IT MAKES ME NAUSEOUS.
- YES, MA'AM.

378
00:33:50,095 --> 00:33:52,829
IT DOES.

379
00:33:56,801 --> 00:33:58,835
<i>[ Boat Horn Blaring ]</i>

380
00:34:03,608 --> 00:34:06,609
-<i> I HAVE TOLD YOU. HE IS GONE.</i>
- SWEEP IT.

381
00:34:06,678 --> 00:34:10,246
YES, MISS PARKER.
WAS THAT A GUN?
WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?

382
00:34:10,315 --> 00:34:13,283
<i>YOU WERE SAYING THAT JAROD</i>
<i>HELPED YOU TO</i>
<i>REMODEL THE MUSEUM.</i>

383
00:34:13,351 --> 00:34:17,587
<i>[ Mr. Kleinman ]</i>
<i>AN ARTIST HE IS,</i>
<i>SENT HERE BY THE ANGELS.</i>

384
00:34:17,655 --> 00:34:23,158
- SO I SEE.
-<i> [ Mr. Kleinman ] HE REDESIGNED</i>
<i>  THE MOVIE STAR EXHIBIT,</i>

385
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:26,061
THE PRESIDENTIAL STUDY
AND MY ROSE ROBE.

386
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:29,832
AND HE EVEN ADDED
A NEW DISPLAY.

387
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:34,903
JAROD CALLS IT...
CENTRE OF SHAME.
SHOW ME.

388
00:34:37,843 --> 00:34:40,343
I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
IT IS SUPPOSED TO MEAN,

389
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:42,645
BUT SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU WILL.

390
00:34:48,619 --> 00:34:50,853
<i> HEY, IT'S US!</i>
<i> [ Chuckling ]</i>

391
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:53,122
<i>INCREDIBLY LIFELIKE.</i>

392
00:34:53,191 --> 00:34:56,392
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>IT JUST GETS WEIRDER</i>
<i>AND WEIRDER.</i>

393
00:35:12,243 --> 00:35:15,011
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> UH-OH. THIS CAN'T BE GOOD.</i>

394
00:35:19,684 --> 00:35:21,483
<i>[ Echoing Laughter ]</i>

395
00:35:21,552 --> 00:35:25,387
- I'LL BE DAMNED!
-<i> [ Broots ] WE JUST WITNESSED</i>
<i>  OUR OWN EXECUTION.</i>

396
00:35:25,456 --> 00:35:28,858
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.
<i>[ Laughter Continues ]</i>

397
00:35:38,035 --> 00:35:40,102
<i>[ Hawk ]</i>
<i>WELCOME TO THE ANGEL'S FLIGHT.</i>

398
00:35:40,171 --> 00:35:42,538
<i>AS I LOOK AT YOU ALL TONIGHT,</i>

399
00:35:42,607 --> 00:35:46,375
<i>I'M FILLED WITH DIVINE ENERGY.</i>

400
00:35:46,444 --> 00:35:50,313
THE BELIEF IN THE POSSIBILITY
OF THE IMPOSSIBLE.

401
00:35:50,382 --> 00:35:54,183
THAT FAITH IS WHAT SEPARATES
THE LEADERS FROM THE FOLLOWERS,

402
00:35:54,252 --> 00:36:00,022
THE ENLIGHTENED FROM THE BLIND,
THE GODS... FROM THE MORTALS.

403
00:36:04,361 --> 00:36:08,430
WITH YOUR STRENGTH AND SPIRIT,
ALL THINGS ARE POSSIBLE.

404
00:36:22,780 --> 00:36:25,548
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LOOKING FOR</i>
<i>YOUR SAFETY LINE, HAWK?</i>

405
00:36:26,651 --> 00:36:30,953
- JAROD.
- YOU SEEM SURPRISED TO SEE ME.

406
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:33,789
I SAW THE SHIRT.
KESSLER SHOT YOU.

407
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:37,593
AH-AH-AH.
THE FIRST RULE OF MAGIC:

408
00:36:39,263 --> 00:36:41,798
<i>NEVER BELIEVE WHAT YOU SEE.</i>

409
00:36:41,866 --> 00:36:44,033
<i>HAWK, WHAT'S GOING ON?</i>

410
00:36:44,101 --> 00:36:49,371
IT SEEMS OUR FRIEND HAWK HERE
ISN'T EXACTLY THE MAGIC MAN
HE PRETENDS TO BE.

411
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:52,809
YOU WANT TO TELL THEM?
OR SHOULD I?

412
00:36:56,547 --> 00:37:01,050
- GO TO HELL.
- YOU FIRST.

413
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:09,992
WHAT'S THAT?
IT'S YOU. AND YOU.
AND YOU.

414
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:11,994
IT'S ALL OF YOU.
GO AHEAD. TAKE A LOOK.

415
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:14,330
HAWK HAD A PERSONAL FILE
ON EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU.

416
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:18,134
<i> HE KNEW WHO YOU WERE,</i>
<i> WHO YOU ARE,</i>
<i> WHERE YOU'RE FROM,</i>

417
00:37:18,203 --> 00:37:21,804
<i> HOW MUCH YOU HAD TO...</i>
<i> OFFER.</i>

418
00:37:21,873 --> 00:37:25,141
<i> HE KNEW YOUR DEEPEST FEARS,</i>
<i> YOUR DARKEST SECRETS.</i>

419
00:37:25,209 --> 00:37:27,142
HE KNEW YOU BETTER
THAN YOU KNEW YOURSELVES.

420
00:37:27,211 --> 00:37:31,848
<i>AND IN RETURN FOR HIS</i>
<i>AMAZING INSIGHTS, YOU GAVE HIM</i>
<i>WHATEVER YOU HAD OF VALUE.</i>

421
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:35,752
<i>AND WHY NOT?</i>
<i>HE SAW INTO YOUR SOULS, RIGHT?</i>

422
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:41,457
- WHY?
- MONEY.

423
00:37:43,361 --> 00:37:45,327
UNFORTUNATELY, NOT ALL OF YOU
WERE SO EASILY LED.

424
00:37:45,396 --> 00:37:48,464
THAT'S WHY YOU
KILLED JESSE BRACKEN.

425
00:37:48,533 --> 00:37:53,469
SHE STUMBLED
ONTO YOUR COMPUTER ROOM,
DISCOVERED YOUR LITTLE SCAM.

426
00:37:53,537 --> 00:37:56,138
<i> AND THAT'S IT.</i>
<i> SHE HAD TO GO.</i>

427
00:37:56,207 --> 00:38:00,375
<i>SO YOU DRAGGED HER UP HERE</i>
<i>AND YOU THREW HER OFF THE ROOF.</i>

428
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:05,047
- YOU CAN'T PROVE ANYTHING.
- CAN'T I?

429
00:38:07,351 --> 00:38:09,351
NEXT TIME YOU TOSS SOMEONE
OFF A BUILDING,

430
00:38:09,420 --> 00:38:13,690
YOU'D BETTER MAKE DAMN SURE
YOU CLEAN UP AFTER YOURSELF.

431
00:38:16,528 --> 00:38:19,294
SO, YOU STILL THINK...

432
00:38:19,363 --> 00:38:22,865
THAT YOU'RE WORTHY TO FLY
WITH THE ANGELS, HAWK?

433
00:38:22,934 --> 00:38:26,835
OR IS THIS JUST
A PATHETIC CURTAIN CALL
OF A HALF-BAKED MAGIC SHOW?

434
00:38:31,209 --> 00:38:35,511
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?
DIVINE INTERVENTION?

435
00:38:48,859 --> 00:38:51,026
<i> [ Hawk ]</i>
<i> MY FINAL GIFT TO YOU.</i>

436
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:05,775
SON OF A BITCH!
YOU KILLED HIM!

437
00:39:05,844 --> 00:39:08,144
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> AH-AH-AH.</i>
<i> REMEMBER WHAT I TOLD YOU?</i>

438
00:39:08,213 --> 00:39:11,780
<i> THE FIRST RULE OF MAGIC:</i>
<i> NEVER BELIEVE WHAT YOU SEE.</i>

439
00:39:28,933 --> 00:39:32,268
<i> I HATE TO SAY IT,</i>
<i> BUT JAROD HAS ME STUMPED</i>
<i> THIS TIME.</i>

440
00:39:32,336 --> 00:39:34,937
THERE MUST BE SOMETHING
THAT WE'RE NOT SEEING.

441
00:39:42,313 --> 00:39:45,080
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>EYES, NOSE, EARS, MOUTH.</i>
<i>IT ALL SEEMS TO BE THERE.</i>

442
00:39:45,149 --> 00:39:48,917
<i>SEE NO EVIL, HEAR NO EVIL,</i>
<i>SPEAK NO EVIL.</i>

443
00:39:48,986 --> 00:39:51,787
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT MEANS,</i>
<i>BUT IT GIVES ME A BAD FEELING.</i>

444
00:39:55,192 --> 00:39:58,127
- GOOD. YOU'RE ALL STILL HERE.
- WHERE ELSE?

445
00:39:58,196 --> 00:40:01,196
AS YOU MAY OR MAY NOT KNOW,
THE TRIUMVIRATE HAS DECIDED...

446
00:40:01,265 --> 00:40:04,934
TO BECOME MORE HANDS-ON
IN THE PURSUIT OF JAROD.

447
00:40:05,003 --> 00:40:07,836
AND IN AN EFFORT TO PROTECT
THE INTEGRITY OF THEIR PURSUIT,

448
00:40:07,905 --> 00:40:10,572
AN ELEMENT HAS BEEN ADDED
TO ACT AS A SAFEGUARD,

449
00:40:10,641 --> 00:40:13,408
<i> OR A SAFETY NET,</i>
<i> IF YOU WILL.</i>

450
00:40:13,477 --> 00:40:15,577
WHY DON'T YOU JUST SAY IT?
A NEW PLAYER.

451
00:40:15,646 --> 00:40:19,748
YOU CAN THINK OF HIM
AS A ONE-MAN
INTERNAL AFFAIRS DIVISION.

452
00:40:21,486 --> 00:40:23,486
MR. COX.

453
00:40:27,191 --> 00:40:30,158
- COX?
- IT'S WITH AN "X."

454
00:40:30,227 --> 00:40:36,131
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>
<i>I HOPE WE GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER</i>
<i>BETTER IN THE COMING DAYS.</i>

455
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:40,169
- NO DOUBT.
- I HATE TO BE RUDE,

456
00:40:40,237 --> 00:40:43,539
<i> BUT WE REALLY HAVE TO LEAVE</i>
<i> IF WE'RE GONNA MAKE</i>
<i> THAT NEXT APPOINTMENT.</i>

457
00:40:59,189 --> 00:41:01,724
THAT ANSWERS THAT.

458
00:41:01,792 --> 00:41:05,862
BRINGS US TO A BIGGER QUESTION.
WHO IS MR. COX?

459
00:41:07,198 --> 00:41:10,299
JAROD ALREADY ANSWERED THAT.

460
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:15,337
HE'S THE GRIM REAPER.

461
00:41:34,558 --> 00:41:39,561
- HI.
- HEY, DETECTIVE WAXMAN. I WAS
HOPING WE'D SEE YOU AGAIN.

462
00:41:39,630 --> 00:41:43,132
I WAS ON MY WAY OUT OF TOWN,
AND I THOUGHT I WOULD
STOP BY AND SAY GOOD-BYE.

463
00:41:43,201 --> 00:41:46,102
<i> YOU LOOK GOOD.</i>
THE DOCTOR SAID IT'S A MIRACLE
SHE WASN'T KILLED.

464
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:50,439
<i>MY DAD SAYS</i>
<i>THAT YOU SAVED MY LIFE.</i>
<i>I DON'T KNOW HOW TO THANK YOU.</i>

465
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:52,774
SEEING YOU SITTING THERE SMILING
IS THANKS ENOUGH.

466
00:41:52,843 --> 00:41:56,678
THEY SAID THE MAN THAT DID THIS
CONFESSED TO RUNNING THE SCAM
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY.

467
00:41:56,747 --> 00:41:59,448
IT'S GOOD TO KNOW HE WON'T BE
HURTING ANYBODY ELSE'S CHILDREN.

468
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:03,586
<i>DETECTIVE,</i>
<i>I KNOW IT'S NOT THE SAME</i>
<i>AS SAVING YOUR LIFE,</i>

469
00:42:03,654 --> 00:42:06,388
BUT I THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU'D LIKE TO HAVE THIS.

470
00:42:06,457 --> 00:42:09,191
IT HELPED KEEP ME SAFE.
I HOPE IT'LL DO
THE SAME FOR YOU.

471
00:42:10,527 --> 00:42:12,928
I'LL KEEP IT CLOSE.
THANK YOU.

472
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:17,199
BYE.
BYE.

